  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>53</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The shadows in the cavern suddenly lengthen and swallow you. When your eyes adjust to the darkness, you find yourself in the midst of what must be another vision.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 2</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can it...? It has to be!" Hiravias squeals with delight. "Wael!" he chirps, "But I never thought he'd reveal himself in person!"

Hiravias' face turns flush and his good eye widens with delight. "This is incredible! Even his form is fickle and unknowable... amazing..." His jaw drops open and his words become slurred, whispered ramblings.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can it be? I never thought I'd see... with my very own eyes!" Hiravias turns pale as he examines the shifting presence.

"Even when you look Wael in the face, you can't know for certain." He bows his head to the figure.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He Who Sees and Is Not Seen... save when he chooses, it seems." Kana regards the figure with wary fascination. "I thought the god of mysteries my chief enemy, at times, but... one cannot seek out answers if the questions aren't there." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>The figure transforms from male to female, from orlan to aumaua, its bones lengthening and its fur receding into its flesh. The only detail that remains constant is the smooth, eyeless face.

The whizzing, rushing shapes from the mist converge on the figure, and as they form a spinning cloud, you realize that they are eyes.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A mightier quarry for a more glorious battle. Yet the hunter takes the rack of antlers and the string of fangs for the memory of hunting the beast, tracking it through the wilds and grappling with it at last."

Wael folds its hands, grinning at you with an orlan's needle-sharp teeth. "Even the gods require fresh mysteries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And yet fresh snowfall covers tracks, and waves wipe footprints from the sand, changing the terrain. This is the landscape of new journeys and uncharted discoveries."

Wael folds its hands, grinning at you with an orlan's needle-sharp teeth. "Even the gods require fresh mysteries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A song the world knows and tires of. A droning chorus repeated again and again. Better the improvised melody, the unfolding chant. The listeners sit rapt, and just when they think they have the tune, it changes again."

Wael folds its hands, grinning at you with an orlan's needle-sharp teeth. "Even the gods require fresh mysteries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"To live out countless lives, each old existence lost to the new. The point is never the end with that last, shuddering breath, but all the years that lead up to it."

Wael folds its hands, grinning at you with an orlan's needle-sharp teeth. "Even the gods require fresh mysteries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But what would happen to the souls?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>The clouds break, and the torrent of rain washes Wael's features clean. His blank face molds itself again, taking on the shape of something you've never seen before. 

"Do not consign the souls to the fate of some god's choosing. You have found them - now scatter them across existence, their destination known to neither god nor mortal. Let them be lost again, new answers to new riddles."

Behind him, the sudden downpour has carved new caves into the canyon.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Farewell, Wael."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You say I shouldn't let a god decide their fate, but it seems you're asking me to do just that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"In a way. But something must be done, and hurling them from the machinery of other schemes is the truest course of action."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>The shifting face laughs. "That is a word for endings, and this is but a crossroads. Even I do not know what you would choose." Shadows from the new caves melt and spread across the landscape, covering you in darkness.

When the light returns, the vision is gone.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You unravel a thread, Watcher. One you have lost and discovered over generations. And following it to its end has only brought you back to the beginning."

The eyes track you even as they circle the god.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you talking about?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Speak plainly."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Another riddling god. Fantastic."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>Wael giggles, a strangely modulated sound that rises and falls as the god shifts from one form to the next. "You seek and search while your foe obscures... and even your quest for answers to your past has only led you to another mystery, and one grander still."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Wael giggles, a strangely modulated sound that rises and falls as the god shifts from one form to the next. "And drain the meaning from the end you have almost achieved? Your search for answers to your past has led you to another mystery, and one grander still."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Which means that you must scatter the very thing she seeks."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm here to stop Woedica from tipping the balance of power."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My goal now is to see to the souls Thaos has trapped."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"These mysteries don't matter to me. I just want to keep my own soul from unraveling."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>Changing from elf to folk, Wael raises its darkening hands to the swarm of eyes. "A nebula of souls, blind and brimming with potential. The answer to Woedica's question and the beginning of yours - what would you do with them?"

Thunder clouds form overhead, casting shadows of movement across the canyon.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Berath wants them returned to the cycle."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"According to Hylea, it's possible to restore them to Hollowborn."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I learned from Galawain, Magran, and Abydon that I can use them to fortify other souls in the Dyrwood."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Rymrgand, Ondra, and Skaen would have me dissolve them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I take it you've got something in mind..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes, but what would you do with them?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yet as you've sought this goal, your foes have pursued another."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The form of the question prepares the seeker for the answer, Watcher. And while you seek to repair your past, Woedica seeks to restore her future."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"None know. They could end up anywhere in the realms of gods or mortals, whole or divided. Discovering them again and charting their course through the ether will be a new mystery."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>Wael giggles, a strangely modulated sound that rises and falls as the god shifts from one form to the next. "Your search for answers to your past has led you to another mystery, and one grander still."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Have I been here before?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What end would that serve?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No end, Watcher! That is the purpose."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>You are surrounded by mists. The ground feel springy under your feet - you imagine that, as soon as you take a step, the soil behind you will erase all trace of your passage.

As if on cue, the mists before you clear just enough for you to take a couple steps forward. You do, and the fog closes behind you. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>You continue for several minutes in this manner, one step at a time, never seeing more than the ground right in front of you. Eventually, rays of light cut through the haze, and you find yourself facing a canyon wall. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 48</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>Pallegina's head violently snaps to one side, her eyes tracking some unseen threat. She puts her hand to the side of her face where two of her feathers have been cut short near the base. Tufts of down float in the air.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>Ed√©r's head twists suddenly, as though something had flown in front of his face. 

"What's that?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>Durance's head twitches, as though a mosquito had flown into his ear. He swings haphazardly at the air with his staff.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>Something whizzes past you. Just as you turn, you catch another whir of movement. Out of the mist flits a shape, small and round. You think you see another. And another. They tickle the corners of your vision.

You turn back to the canyon wall. The sun shifts along its path, and what looked like a smooth rock face is the hollow of a cave. A figure steps out, its features shifting and changing before your eyes.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You understand the value of a mystery, Watcher. A buried scroll, a hidden truth. These are my ways."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You inhabit the narrow space between answers and questions, embracing riddles with no answers. You ask simply for the glory of the question."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>{DEBUG: this is the list of rep conditionals that would be attached to the node above. Instead, This set of conditionals and those attached to the other nodes in this layer should control whether or not the Wael encounter spawns}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your very past is a mystery. You bury it deep, reinventing yourself with each new path."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You are a creature of contradictions. By turns cruel and kind, rational and zealous, your nature is buffeted by forces and whims that none can anticipate."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your fingers explore the very fabric of reality. You live to uncover answers, yet the questions you leave in your wake will outlast even your discoveries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
